## REQUIREMENTS FOR THE BUSINESS ROUTE

### Content Format
- All business posts must be `.mdx` format
- Frontmatter must be extremely advanced ‚Äî SEO, GEO, AEO fields all included
- Schema must be expandable ‚Äî adding a new region = adding one `.mdx` file

### Frontmatter Must Include (at minimum ‚Äî you may suggest more after research)
- Core: `slug`, `title`, `excerpt`, `date`, `dateModified`, `author`
- Region: `region`, `regionCode`, `language`, `locale`
- SEO: `canonical`, `targetKeyword`, `secondaryKeywords`, `searchIntent`, `noIndex`
- GEO/AEO: `faqSchema` (array of Q&A pairs baked into frontmatter), `entityType`, `speakable`
- Contact: `contact` object (email, whatsapp, instagram)
- Services: `services` array
- Schema: `schemaType` field to control JSON-LD output
- Display: `template`, `image`, `imageAlt`, `imageWidth`, `imageHeight`

### SEO / GEO / AEO Requirements
- JSON-LD schema: `LocalBusiness` or `ProfessionalService` ‚Äî NOT `Article`
- FAQ schema injected from frontmatter `faqSchema` array
- Breadcrumb schema
- `hreflang` support via `regionCode` + `language` frontmatter
- Canonical per page
- `noIndex` frontmatter field respected in robots meta
- OG type: `website` (not `article`)
- Speakable schema if `speakable: true` in frontmatter
- Every page must have a unique `targetKeyword` ‚Äî never duplicated

### Code Rules
- TypeScript strict ‚Äî no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
- Tailwind only ‚Äî no inline styles, no new CSS files
- Use `next/image` for all images
- Use exact font names, colour tokens, class names from `globals.css` and `tailwind.config.js` ‚Äî do not invent new ones
- Do NOT modify any existing file
- Do NOT touch: `src/lib/blog.ts`, `src/types/blog.ts`, `src/app/blog/**`, `src/lib/generateSchemas.ts`
- `gray-matter`, `marked`, `next-mdx-remote` already installed ‚Äî use them
- Mobile-first, fully responsive ‚Äî desktop and mobile both must look excellent

### Deliverable Rules
- Every file in a code artifact
- Artifacts must be complete and copy-paste ready
- Example `.mdx` post must be realistic enough to fully test the page visually
